ServiceNow Access: Simplify Your Request Process!
Introduction
This article provides an overview of raising access requests to ServiceNow. As part of the User Access Harmonization (UAH) initiative, a standardized way for requesting and managing ServiceNow access for all Novartis associates is implemented starting in 2021.

With the help of Request Access to ServiceNow Catalog Item associates (with Novartis 521 UserID) can raise Single User Access requests, Bulk user access for either themselves or for someone else.
The Catalog Item also offers a Revoke User Access option for submitting access request removal requests.
ServiceNow access requests are fulfilled after approvals. Provisioning is automated through group membership. Training completion may be required before access is granted, and this is checked automatically for certain requests.
In Scope
All-access requests for regular ServiceNow applications (Single user access, bulk user access, access removals).
This KB article outlines the general content of the ServiceNow access request form used across all organizations and applications on the platform.
Out of Scope
Specialist access is provisioned for administrators, which is handled separately at the ServiceNow Platform level.
Organization/Application-specific configurations of the Request Access to ServiceNow Catalog Item.

